<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Pennywise]]></name></author>
<updated>2018-08-04T15:41:33-07:00</updated>
<published>2018-08-04T15:41:33-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17628&amp;p=222678#p222678</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17628&amp;p=222678#p222678"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Possible vblank issue with text getting written to screen]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17628&amp;p=222678#p222678"><![CDATA[
So, I'm translating this simple game and it's pretty much finished, but there's an issue with longer text printing to the screen. I think I know what the issue is, but was hoping to get a second opinion.<br /><br />Anyhow, I've debugged the game a bit and was able to determine that it's not an issue with the game reading the text data from the ROM.  I believe the issue is that due to the extended length, the game runs out of time for vblank and text doesn't get printed as a result.<br /><br /><img src="https://images2.imgbox.com/03/82/Yfn7hOKx_o.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />It should say &quot;Not enough money!&quot; That character at the end is a ryo and a relic from the previous string. Fun fact, the game clears previous strings by just overwriting the old string with the new one. This one's probably a better example.<br /><br /><img src="https://images2.imgbox.com/1a/27/WHPEEMmb_o.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Anyhow, sometimes it will print no problems and other times not so much.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3981">Pennywise</a> — Sat Aug 04, 2018 3:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
